  #program
    %h2 Program
    %h3 Wednesday, November 2
    :markdown
      **Welcome dinner:** Dinner with all the attendees and local hackers and entrepreneurs that are hosting us.
    %h3 Thursday, November 3
    :markdown
      **El Futuro:** [El Futuro Conference](http://elfuturo.mx) is taking place during Thursday and Friday. El Futuro is one of the mayor web and digital media conferences in Mexico. We are attending the first day to enjoy some keynotes, but especially to know some of the local players and interact with the.
    %h3 Friday, November 4
    :markdown  
      **Expedition to Palenque:** One of the most beautiful mayan sites on planet Earth, Palenque is just three hours away from Villahermosa, our basecamp. We are visiting for the day and we're spending the night in bungalows in the middle of the jungle. 
    %h3 Saturday, November 5
    :markdown
      **SuperHappyDevHouse:** Saturday is hack day. SuperHappyDevHouse is a party for hackers and thinkers, or put differently, a hackathon just for fun. It is a great opportunity to work on personal projects and learn from collaborating with others. 
    %h3 Sunday, November 6
    :markdown
      **Expedition to Kolemchen:** One of the most beautiful natural reserves in the state, Kolemchen is also a couple of hours away from Villahermosa. 
  #getting_there
    %h2 Getting there
    %h3 From Mexico City
    %p We have a sponsored bus that departing from Mexico City. The same bus will drive us during the Hackspedition and will return us to Mexico City by the end of the weekend. 
    %h3 From Houston, TX
    %p Continental Airlines operates a daily evening flight directly to Villahermosa, Tabasco.
